        "rich_text_ccxpK9": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Ring shopping can be overwhelming, especially when there are so many diamond shapes and cuts for you to choose the perfect one. Rings that are made out of precious metals such as gold and platinum are designed for milestone moments - to mark the moments with something just as grand as the moment. If you are looking for a guide to help you through the different types of ring shapes and cuts, you have come to the right place. At <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry\">Lucira Jewelry</a>, our entire collection is lab grown diamond certified. Our grown diamond ring shapes and cuts are crafted to last forever, each having its own beauty. This guide covers everything you need to know about cuts and shapes, from the types to who they are ideal for. </p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_kKqW7n": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": " Shape & Diamond Cut",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Understanding the Difference Between Diamond Shape & Diamond Cuts</h2>",
            "custom_id": "understanding",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_KhakP7": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Shapes_Cut_16_9.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_kcy6qD": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": " Shape & Diamond Cut P1",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>It is common to get confused between a diamond’s shape and cut, but they are different. Diamond shapes mean the external outline, such as round, oval, pear, square or any silhouette that determines the shape of the diamond. Diamond cuts, on the other side, mean the proportions and the finish of the diamond, such as bezel or emerald. The diamond shape and cut determine the overall look of the diamond, including the way it reflects light and shines. Essentially speaking, a diamond shape is the shape of the ring that you see from above, and a diamond cut is the way you see the diamond sign. Apart from the popular shapes and cuts, a lab grown diamond ring comes with different options in both shapes and cuts, letting you customize the look the way you wish! <br/><br/></p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_BxFmqg": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Exploring Diamond Shapes",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Exploring Diamond Shapes</h2><p>Let’s first have a look at the different types of diamond shapes. Cultured diamonds come in a wide range of shapes, making it challenging to choose one. Each diamond shape has its distinct aura, and to decide which one is the most <em>you, </em>we have listed below not only the different shapes, but the kind of look each one provides, and who is that shape ideal for. <br/></p>",
            "custom_id": "exploring",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_znfWE9": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Round Brilliant",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Round Brilliant - The Timeless Sparklee</h3>",
